== Aeronautical operations technician ==


{{translated page|fr|Technicien a<U+00E9>ronautique d'exploitation|version=74685523|insertversion=74685523|section=}}

The degree of '''Technicien a<U+00E9>ronautique d'exploitation''' (TAE, in English '''Aeronautical operations technician''') is a certification created in 2011. It is a title recognized by [[Commission nationale de la certification professionnelle|CNCP]]<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.legifrance.gouv.fr/affichTexte.do?cidTexte=JORFTEXT000024846790 Arr<U+00EA>t<U+00E9> du 17 novembre 2011 portant enregistrement au r<U+00E9>pertoire national des certifications professionnelles]</ref>, and recorded level IV in the [[National Classification of Levels of Training]]. The graduation is after a training at the ''[[<U+00C9>cole nationale de l'aviation civile]]'' (French civil aviation university).

== History ==
The TAE course started in 1962<ref>{{fr}}Book ''50 ans d'<U+00C9>nac au service de l'aviation, <U+00C9>dition S.E.E.P.P, 1999'' p.245</ref>. It was originally named <U+00AB> ''Agent d'Exploitation'' <U+00BB> (Handling Agent / [[Flight Dispatcher]]). The new name was introduced in November 2010<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.cge-news.com/contenus/180/cms_pc/fichier/169/101122153310_lettre_-enac.pdf La lettre d'information mensuelle de l'<U+00C9>cole Nationale de l'Aviation Civile]</ref>.

== Application ==
The students have three possibilities to integrate the course :
* [[Competitive examination]] organized by [[<U+00C9>cole nationale de l'aviation civile|ENAC]] each year ;
* French ''[[Baccalaur<U+00E9>at]]'' and two years of working in the air transport industry<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.letudiant.fr/etudes/annuaire-enseignement-superieur/formation/formation-agent-d-exploitation-11687.html Technicien a<U+00E9>ronautique d'exploitation (TAE) - ENAC Toulouse]</ref> ;
* Students from the preparation for the [[Airline Transport Pilot Licence]] theory (CPATPL) course of [[<U+00C9>cole nationale de l'aviation civile|ENAC]]<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.aerobuzz.fr/spip.php?article2286 L<U+2019>ENAC ouvre un cycle pr<U+00E9>paratoire <U+00E0> l<U+2019>ATPL destin<U+00E9> aux boursiers]</ref>.

== Training ==
The training is in seven months in [[Toulouse]] or, since September 2012<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.lemonde.fr/orientation-scolaire/article/2011/06/21/un-professionnel-de-l-aeronautique-trouvera-du-travail-dans-tous-les-secteurs_1537364_1473696.html "Un professionnel de l'a<U+00E9>ronautique trouvera du travail dans tous les secteurs"]</ref>, on the Aerocampus <U+00BB> of [[Latresne]]<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.enac.fr/fr/newsletter-enac-n<U+00B0>98-novembre-2011 Newsletter ENAC - n<U+00B0>98 / Novembre 2011]</ref> in a [[dual education system]]. The curriculum propose, in substantially equal parts, general lessons of [[aeronautics]] and practical lessons : [[air navigation]], [[Telecommunication|telecommunications]] and aeronautical information, [[aircraft flight mechanics]], navigation, [[avionics]], [[meteorology]], air operations, [[air law]], english, ....

The course ends by a four weeks [[internship]]<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.enac.fr/fr/system/files/tae_0.pdf Pr<U+00E9>sentation de la formation Technicien A<U+00E9>ronautique d<U+2019>Exploitation]</ref>.

== Occupations ==
The ''Technicien a<U+00E9>ronautique d'exploitation'' is responsible for the flight preparation and [[flight planning]], passengers, freight management and pricing. he works for an [[airline]] or an [[airport]]<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.studya.com/formations_metiers/aeronautique/agent_exploitation.htm  L'Agent d'exploitation a<U+00E9>ronautique]</ref>.

== Personality related ==
* Joel Laitselart (Promotion 1987), air operations teacher at [[<U+00C9>cole nationale de l'aviation civile|ENAC]] and former operations manager of [[Aeris (airline)|Aeris]]<ref>{{fr}}[http://www.ladepeche.fr/article/2001/02/02/543286-indiscretion-aeris-recapitalisee-pour-de-nouveaux-projets.html Indiscr<U+00E9>tion : A<U+00E9>ris recapitalis<U+00E9>e pour de nouveaux projets.]</ref>.

